cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses learning in neuroscience and machine learning, specifically developing competitive Hebbian learning algorithms for sparse, distributed neural codes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the paper's focus on learning algorithms and neural codes. cs.CV is also likely, given the paper's use of deep convolutional nets for image datasets. cs.AI and cs.SY are less likely, but still possible, as the paper touches on unsupervised learning and adaptation.
